## Pear Shaped Diamond Ring by Metal: White Gold, Yellow Gold, Rose Gold & Platinum

Each metal creates a fundamentally different ring — same stone, different personality. This is The Metal Multiplier Effect in action.

### Pear Shaped Diamond Ring in White Gold

White gold is the most popular metal for pear diamond rings, particularly in the 14k and 18k varieties. It reads like platinum visually at roughly 30–40% less in setting cost. The important note: white gold requires rhodium plating to maintain its white finish, typically every 1–3 years depending on wear. Platinum never needs replating.

**Best for:** D–H color pear diamonds; buyers who want the white-metal look without the platinum price premium; modern, minimalist styles.

### Pear Shaped Diamond Ring in Yellow Gold

Yellow gold pear diamond rings have become dramatically more popular since {{year}} - 5. The warm metal amplifies the romantic, vintage character of the pear shape. It also provides the strongest Metal Multiplier benefit — an I or J color diamond looks two grades whiter in yellow gold than it does in platinum.

**Best for:** G–J color pear diamonds; vintage-style settings; buyers who want the maximum stone at a given total budget; rose-colored fancy diamonds.

The Pear Sidestone Diamond Engagement Ring in Yellow Gold at **[$1,820](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/pear-sidestone-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-4-ct-tw-item-192877?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** is a standout here. It is specifically designed for the pear shape, with side stones that taper alongside the belly and a prong configuration built for pear proportions. It also comes in white gold and rose gold.

### Pear Shaped Diamond Ring in Rose Gold

Rose gold has a softness that suits the pear shape particularly well. The teardrop silhouette reads romantic and feminine in rose gold in a way that no other metal replicates. It is also excellent for fancy colored pear diamonds — pink, champagne, and brown/chocolate diamonds read beautifully against the warm rose-copper tone.

**Best for:** H–J color natural pear diamonds; fancy colored pear diamonds; buyers who want a distinctive, romantic look; vintage-style and floral settings.

[![Pear shaped diamond ring in rose gold solitaire setting — warm copper-pink metal with white pear diamond](/images/pear-shaped-diamond-ring-solitaire-rose-gold.avif)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Pear&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)
*Rose gold pear shaped diamond ring — the warm pink metal flatters H–J color diamonds and fancy colored stones equally. **[See rose gold pear rings on Blue Nile →](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Pear&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)***

### Pear Shaped Diamond Ring in Platinum

Platinum is the premium choice for pear diamond rings. It is harder than gold alloys, holds prongs more securely over decades of wear, and never changes color or requires replating. The V-prong holding the tip of your pear diamond will maintain its shape and grip better in platinum over a 20–30 year lifespan.

**Best for:** D–G color pear diamonds; buyers who wear their ring daily without removing it; long-term investment pieces; buyers who want zero maintenance.

