## Unique Pear Diamond Ring Styles: Chocolate, Canary, Blue, Sapphire Accent, Trillion Three-Stone & More

### Chocolate Brown Pear Diamond Ring

Chocolate or brown fancy color pear diamonds are a significantly more affordable entry point into fancy color than yellow or pink. A 1ct chocolate pear diamond can cost $800–$2,500 vs. $15,000–$30,000 for a true yellow fancy. Set in rose gold or yellow gold with a warm metal tone, the brown reads rich and earthy — not muddy.

The key specification: look for a "light brown" or "fancy light brown" grade from GIA, not just a commercial "chocolate" designation. Brown diamonds without a GIA fancy color grade are often I2–I3 clarity natural-color diamonds that happen to be brown — not the same quality tier.

### Yellow (Canary) Pear Diamond Ring

Fancy yellow pear diamonds are the most popular fancy color in the pear shape. The elongated silhouette maximizes the saturation display of the yellow tone across the face of the stone. "Fancy Intense Yellow" is the GIA grade that corresponds to what the market calls "canary."

A 1ct Fancy Intense Yellow pear from Blue Nile runs **$8,000–$15,000** — significantly more than a white pear at the same weight but a fraction of what the round equivalent costs. Set in yellow gold to maximize the color saturation.

### Blue Pear Diamond Ring

Natural blue diamonds are among the rarest materials on Earth. A 1ct natural blue pear will range from **$50,000 to $300,000+** depending on saturation and GIA color grade. They are investment pieces, not everyday jewelry decisions.

Lab-grown blue pear diamonds are a more accessible alternative: lab blue CVD diamonds with a strong blue body color run $3,000–$8,000 per carat depending on size and saturation. Set in platinum to maximize the cool blue tone. White gold or platinum is mandatory — yellow or rose gold will visually suppress the blue.

### Pear Shaped Diamond Ring with Sapphire Accent

The sapphire-and-pear-diamond combination is one of the most distinctive looks in the engagement ring market. The Classic Pear Shaped Sapphire Ring in platinum at **[$2,610](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-pear-shaped-sapphire-engagement-ring-in-platinum-item-194499?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** uses a pear sapphire as the center stone with diamond accents — a completely different aesthetic from a white diamond with sapphire accents.

If you want a white pear diamond center with sapphire side stones, a custom setting is typically required. Blue Nile's standard catalog doesn't offer this configuration off the shelf, but most local jewelers can source oval or pear sapphire side stones and set them alongside a pear diamond center.

### Trillion Three-Stone Pear Diamond Ring

The three-stone configuration with trillion side stones is one of the most flattering settings for a pear center diamond. The triangular silhouette of the trillion mirrors the pointed shape of the pear, creating visual coherence between the center and the sides.

The proportioning rule: trillion side stones should be approximately 30–40% of the center stone's face width. A 1ct pear center with 0.30–0.35ct trillion sides reads balanced. Larger trillions visually compete with the pear; smaller ones disappear.

This configuration is typically built as a custom piece or modified setting — it is not a standard Blue Nile catalog option. Build it by selecting a three-stone setting base and discussing trillion replacement with the retailer. See the **[three-stone pear diamond ring guide](/three-stone-pear-diamond-ring)** for a full breakdown of side-stone options and pricing.

### Pear Cut Diamond with Baguettes

Baguette side stones are one of the most architecturally striking pairings for a pear center diamond. The rectangular step-cut geometry of the baguette creates a deliberate contrast against the curved belly and tapered point of the pear — an intentional tension between shapes that defines Art Deco and modern geometric ring design.

A pear shaped diamond with baguettes reads structured and editorial. The baguettes must be set with their long axis running parallel to the belly of the pear, not angled outward. Angled baguettes pull the eye away from the pear silhouette; parallel baguettes frame it cleanly.

Proportion rule: baguette length should be 60–70% of the pear's width at its widest point. Too long and the baguettes visually compete with the center stone; too short and they read as accidental accents rather than intentional design. A 1ct pear diamond with baguettes typically pairs best with two 0.15–0.20ct baguettes on either side.

Blue Nile does not carry a standard catalog setting with baguette side stones for pear centers — this is a custom-build category. Work with a local bench jeweler or a specialty custom setting service. Estate and antique markets also carry original Art Deco pieces with pear diamond and baguette configurations from the 1920s–1940s that are worth searching.

### Pear Cluster Diamond Ring

A pear cluster diamond ring groups multiple pear-shaped diamonds — or a mix of pear and round diamonds — into a single arrangement that reads as one large statement piece. It is one of the most visually impactful styles in pear shaped diamond jewelry, and one of the most cost-efficient ways to maximize face-up size.

Two common pear shaped cluster diamond ring configurations:

**Radiating cluster:** Five to seven pear diamonds set point-inward around a small round center brilliant, radiating outward like flower petals. The total face-up coverage of the cluster can equal or exceed a 2ct solitaire at a fraction of the price — individual 0.10–0.25ct pear stones cost significantly less per carat than a single large stone.

**Shoulder cluster:** One larger pear center with cascading clusters of round or pear diamonds set into the shoulders of the shank, creating a bouquet or waterfall effect on either side of the center stone.

The pear cluster is a custom or pre-set configuration — it is not available in Blue Nile's "Design Your Own Ring" system. Victorian and Edwardian estate jewelry is the most fertile ground for authentic vintage pear cluster pieces; modern custom jewelers can recreate the style with new stones. If you want multiple pear stones in a setting without going fully custom, the **[three-stone pear diamond ring](/three-stone-pear-diamond-ring)** is the closest off-the-shelf option — a center pear flanked by two smaller pear or trillion side stones.

### Pear Diamond Halo Ring

[![Pear shaped diamond ring with pavé setting in white gold — French pavé accent diamonds along the shank](/images/pear-shaped-diamond-ring-pave-white-gold.avif)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Pear&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)
*Pavé pear shaped diamond ring in white gold — micro-set accent diamonds along the shank amplify brilliance without competing with the center stone. **[Shop pavé pear diamond rings →](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Pear&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)***

The Pear Shape Side Stone Diamond Halo by James Allen — available on Blue Nile — is the best off-the-shelf halo option for pear diamonds. At **[$3,570 in white or yellow gold](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/pear-shape-side-stone-diamond-halo-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-310842?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** (or **[$4,005 in platinum](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/pear-shape-side-stone-diamond-halo-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-310847?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**), it uses a true pear-outline halo rather than a mismatched round or oval frame. The side diamonds taper along the belly and the halo frames the entire silhouette.

A halo adds apparent size — a 0.80ct pear in a halo reads closer to 1ct face-up. If you are working with a budget that puts a 1ct natural pear out of reach, a halo on a 0.80ct stone is a legitimate strategy. For the full halo comparison including double halo and floating halo styles, see the **[pear diamond halo ring guide](/pear-diamond-halo-ring)**.

