## Vintage Pear Shaped Diamond Ring

Vintage pear diamond rings read differently from modern ones. The defining features: milgrain edging (tiny metal beads along setting edges), hand-engraved shanks, filigree scroll work, and open-work prong designs with architectural detail. Yellow gold is the dominant metal for true vintage pieces; platinum and white gold appear in Art Deco pieces from the 1920s–1930s.

[![Pear shaped diamond ring in white gold cathedral solitaire setting — elevated center stone above the shank](/images/pear-shaped-diamond-ring-cathedral-white-gold.avif)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Pear&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)
*Cathedral solitaire pear shaped diamond ring — the elevated setting makes the elongated pear silhouette more dramatic. Available in white gold, yellow gold, rose gold, and platinum. **[View cathedral settings on Blue Nile →](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Pear&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)***

For vintage-style at a modern price, the Milgrain Lace Pavé Vintage-Style Engagement Ring by James Allen is the strongest catalog option. At **[$2,650 in white or rose gold](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/milgrain-lace-pave-vintage-style-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-315055?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)** and **[$3,250 in platinum](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/milgrain-lace-pave-vintage-style-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-315054?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**, it combines milgrain edging, pavé stones, and lace-like metalwork that reads genuinely period-inspired rather than generic "vintage look."

The pear cut is historically one of the most period-appropriate shapes for vintage settings — it was extremely popular in Victorian and Edwardian jewelry, often in yellow gold and silver-top-gold constructions. A vintage-style setting honors that heritage.

