>
> Make The Orientation Decision before you buy the setting. Make The Metal Multiplier Effect work for your budget before you fix your color grade. A G in yellow gold buys you a better clarity grade than a G in platinum at the same spend — and no one at the dinner table will see the difference in color.
>
> The V-prong at the tip is not optional. If a retailer tells you it is, walk away." — Farzana Hasan, **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**

